## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — Severity-Ranked Findings

This test suite is a textbook example of **"coverage-only" testing** — every production method is called, achieving line coverage, but almost nothing is actually verified. Here are the findings:

---

### 🔴 Critical — No Meaningful Assertions

| # | Test | Anti-Pattern | What can break undetected |
|---|------|-------------|---------------------------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | **Fire-and-forget** — no assert at all | `Save()` could silently no-op; duplicates never caught |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-35) | **Fire-and-forget** — no assert | Price could stay at 9.99 forever; wrong product updated |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` (L38-42) | **Fire-and-forget** — no assert | Product could remain in store |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | **Fire-and-forget** — result discarded | Could return -1 and pass |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | **Fire-and-forget** — no assert | Discount math could be inverted (multiply instead of reduce) |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L84-88) | **Fire-and-forget** — no assert | Parsing could corrupt data; products never actually saved |

---

### 🟠 High — Weak/Tautological Assertions

| # | Test | Anti-Pattern | Fix |
|---|------|-------------|-----|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` (L26-29) | **Assert.IsNotNull only** — never checks the returned values | Could return wrong SKU, wrong price |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` (L47-52) | **Assert.IsNotNull on a List** — `List<T>` is never null from LINQ | Could return 0 results or wrong results |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | **Assert.IsNotNull on a List** — same tautology | Could return empty list |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77-82) | **Assert.IsNotNull on string** — `string.Join` never returns null | CSV could be malformed garbage |

---

### 🟡 Medium — Missing Negative / Edge-Case Tests

| # | Missing scenario | Risk |
|---|-----------------|------|
| 11 | `UpdatePrice` with non-existent SKU | `KeyNotFoundException` path untested |
| 12 | `GetProduct` for missing SKU | Null-return path untested |
| 13 | `Search` with no matches | Empty-result behavior untested |
| 14 | `ImportFromCsv` with malformed input | Will throw `IndexOutOfRangeException` in production |
| 15 | `ApplyBulkDiscount` with fraction > 1 or negative | Negative prices possible |

---

### Concrete Fixes (examples)

```csharp
// #1 — AddProduct: verify round-trip
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_PersistsProduct()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
