### Summary

**Root cause:** Every test follows a "call it and pray" pattern — the suite touches 100% of lines but asserts almost nothing. This gives false confidence via coverage metrics while letting logic bugs (wrong math, no-op writes, malformed output) ship to production. The fix is straightforward: **assert on observable state changes, not just non-nullity.**
